				<div class="single-content-center">
					<p>Starting a business in the UAE can be an exciting and rewarding venture. The country offers
						investor-friendly regulations, attractive tax rates, access to a large talent pool, and
						world-class infrastructure. The UAE is also a dynamic base to reach the nearby markets across
						the Middle East, Africa, Asia and Europe.</p>
					<h4><strong>1.</strong>IT Solutions Company</h4>
					<p>With a growing demand for technology solutions and a business-friendly environment, the UAE
						presents numerous opportunities for entrepreneurs. The country’s high quality of life also makes
						it easy for you to attract talented professionals from diverse backgrounds to help build your
						business. The newly launched Dubai Economic Agenda ‘D33’ aims to accelerate growth by investing
						in advanced technology, opening endless opportunities for tech talents to thrive.</p>
					<h4><strong>2.</strong>Human Resources Consultancy Services</h4>
					<p>Starting a human resources consultancy business presents an excellent opportunity to leverage the
						fruitful economic environment and the growing presence of multinational companies. There is a
						high demand for services such as developing recruitment criteria and job descriptions,
						conducting job interviews, employee training, and performance management, amongst other
						HR-related activities.</p>
					<h4><strong>3.</strong>E-Commerce Business</h4>
					<p>UAE has the highest e-commerce penetration rate in the Middle East and the number is expected to
						reach $9.2 billion by 2026! With a rapidly growing population of online shoppers and a
						supportive government, the opportunities here are endless.</p>
					<p>Business owners can benefit from favorable corporate tax regulations and access to sophisticated
						logistic networks, digital payment systems, and skilled professionals.</p>
					<p>Further advantages include ample research and development assistance, and various e-commerce
						incentives from local governments, which promote the growth of this industry.</p>
					<h4><strong>4.</strong>Event Management Company</h4>
					<p>The event management industry is on the rise in the UAE, especially in Dubai. Many are choosing
						the city as their dream wedding destination. With the recent changes in the civil marriage law,
						this trend is expected to increase exponentially.</p>
					<p>It doesn’t stop there; being a business hub, Dubai hosts international business meetings and
						forums, which require event management services.</p>
					<h4><strong>5.</strong>Green Building Materials Business</h4>
					<p>Dubai and the UAE, in general, are advancing steadily toward a greener future by implementing
						environment-friendly policies in different sectors, including construction. In fact, the country
						has announced 2023 to be the Year of Sustainability.</p>
					<p>Choosing to start a green building materials business will not be profitable but also contribute
						to a higher goal of maintaining a healthy environment for future generations.</p>
					<h3>Why Choose a Free Zone?</h3>
					<figure>
						<picture>
							<source
								srcset="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/assets/images/single-detail.webp"
